## Example Invocation

```
User: "Design the pricing page"

Agent:
1. Check .stitch/designs/pricing/baton.md â†’ not found, start fresh at Round 1
2. Check .stitch/DESIGN.md â†’ missing, auto-generate from design-philosophy.md

=== ROUND 1 ===
3. Design thinking exercise:
   - Aesthetic: Brutalist raw with sharp typography
   - Typography: Display (Space Mono Bold), Body (IBM Plex Sans)
   - Color: Monochrome with neon green accent (#00FF41)
   - Motion: Staggered fade-in on scroll
   - Spatial: Asymmetric grid with diagonal pricing cards
   - Unforgettable element: Oversized pricing numbers that break grid bounds
4. Generate Round 1 PC design (generate_screen_from_text, DESKTOP)
5. get_screen â†’ download PC PNG â†’ save as round-01-pc.png
6. Generate Round 1 Mobile design (generate_screen_from_text, MOBILE)
7. get_screen â†’ download Mobile PNG â†’ save as round-01-mobile.png
8. Append Round 1 review to review.md
9. Update baton â†’ round: 2, base-pc-id, base-mobile-id

=== ROUND 2 ===
10. Design thinking exercise (Visual Identity focus)
11. Review round-01-pc.png and round-01-mobile.png:
    - Section-by-section critique
    - Cross-device parity check
    - Layout issues
    - Style consistency (first page, so establish baseline)
12. Generate Round 2 PC edit (edit_screens, DESKTOP, base = round 1 PC)
13. get_screen â†’ download PC PNG â†’ save as round-02-pc.png
14. Generate Round 2 Mobile edit (edit_screens, MOBILE, base = round 1 Mobile)
15. get_screen â†’ download Mobile PNG â†’ save as round-02-mobile.png
16. Append Round 2 review to review.md
17. Update baton â†’ round: 3

=== ROUNDS 3-5 ===
18. For each round:
    - Review previous round PNGs
    - Section-by-section critique
    - Edit PC + Mobile
    - Download PC + Mobile PNGs
    - Append review
    - Update baton

=== ROUND 6 ===
19. Review round-05-pc.png and round-05-mobile.png
20. Edit PC + Mobile for final polish
21. Download round-06-pc.png and round-06-mobile.png
22. Append Round 6 review to review.md
23. Quality check:
    âś… No layout defects
    âś… Cross-device parity maintained
    âś… Full-bleed integrity confirmed
    âś… Aesthetic vision realized
    âś… Accessibility criteria met
24. Quality PASSES â†’ set status: approved

=== CODE IMPLEMENTATION ===
25. get_screen (approved PC screen) â†’ download HTML â†’ save as round-06-pc.html
26. get_screen (approved Mobile screen) â†’ download HTML â†’ save as round-06-mobile.html
27. Hand off to coding-fe:
    - HTML paths: round-06-pc.html, round-06-mobile.html
    - Route: /pricing
    - Screen name: pricing
```

**If quality check FAILS at step 23:**
```
23. Quality FAILS â†’ document defects in review.md
24. Update baton â†’ round: 7, status: refining
25. Continue from Step 3 (pre-generation review) for Round 7
```

## Anti-Patterns

âťŚ **Skipping rounds** â€” Every screen needs all 6 rounds  
âťŚ **Generic aesthetics** â€” Inter font, purple gradients, cookie-cutter layouts  
âťŚ **Missing design thinking** â€” Rounds 1 & 2 require aesthetic exercise  
âťŚ **Code before approval** â€” HTML downloaded only after round 6 passes quality check  
âťŚ **Style drift** â€” New pages must match existing pages' visual language  
âťŚ **Mobile downscaling** â€” Keep mobile PNGs at highest export resolution  
âťŚ **Skipping PNG downloads** â€” Every round MUST download both PC and Mobile PNGs  
âťŚ **Skipping review** â€” Rounds 2+ require section-by-section critique before editing  
âťŚ **Downloading HTML for review rounds** â€” HTML only for approved implementation round  

## Success Patterns

âś… **Bold aesthetic choices** â€” Commit to an extreme and execute with precision  
âś… **Distinctive typography** â€” Avoid generic fonts, pair display + body thoughtfully  
âś… **Delta-only edits** â€” Round 2+ prompts describe changes, not full spec  
âś… **Section-by-section review** â€” Explicit critique before each edit round  
âś… **Cross-device parity** â€” All core sections present on PC and Mobile  
âś… **Style consistency** â€” Every page feels part of the same design system  
âś… **PNG downloads mandatory** â€” After every round, download both PC and Mobile screenshots for review  
âś… **Cumulative review log** â€” Single review.md file per screen with all rounds documented  
âś… **HTML only when approved** â€” Download HTML exclusively for the locked implementation round  
